jtlee wrote a review Feb 2024
Hong Kong11 contributions22 helpful votes
Lovely Easter family holiday at this resort
Took the family here for Easter. Great weather for that time of year. Loved the property with the tram service that scales the hill to take you from the villas and rooms to the beach. The buggy service was also excellent. Spent most of our time on the beach and in the pool. The room was spacious and well designed. Also had a monkey visit on our balcony which was equal parts amusing and fascinating! Had a grown-ups only dinner at La Maison 1888 which was exquisite. The head sommelier, Jimmy was a standout with his spot-on pairings and down to earth personality. Used the in-room babysitting and felt at ease with the kind and attentive staff. Also then hotel manager, Seif was such lovely and friendly character who took care of ours and our children’s needs. Would highly recommend…
Date of stay: April 2023
